**Overall Meaning:**

"May my mind be filled with auspicious thoughts, I know this great person, sun-colored, beyond darkness, whose source the wise see."

**Explanation:**

This verse describes a profound understanding of the divine. The speaker asserts their knowledge of this "great person," who is characterized as being "sun-colored," symbolizing radiance, enlightenment, and the source of all light. This divine being is said to exist beyond darkness, signifying a realm of pure consciousness and infinite knowledge. The verse emphasizes that only the wise can truly perceive the source of this divine being, highlighting the importance of spiritual insight and wisdom in understanding the ultimate reality. 


